HEADWORD: Decipium
<hw>De*cip"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>decipere</ets> to deceive.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
supposed rare element, said to be associated with cerium, yttrium, etc.,
in the mineral samarskite, and more recently called <xex>samarium</xex>.
Symbol Dp. See <er>Samarium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
